records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kurtis J Sprengel in court with attorney Dawn M. Rablin.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.
Court sentenced defendant to serve 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 2 days served; Huber privileges for work and treatment. Court does not recommends against electronic monitoring. Report by 10/27/2014 by 3pm.  Failure to report will result in a straight time sentence.  Court authorize transfer to Dodge county.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges by 7/10/2015 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.

Filed,
